item.title: Singapore and Jiangsu strengthen economic ties
item.description:
The Singapore-Jiangsu Cooperation Council (SJCC) aims to boost opportunities for companies from both regions in areas like collaboration in third-party markets, trade and logistics, and financial services. This contributes to the existing Singapore-Jiangsu economic partnership and advances the Belt and Road Initiative (BRI). Thirteen memoranda of understanding (MoUs) reflect these goals. Singapore’s Finance Minister, Heng Swee Keat, who is also SJCC Co-Chairman, emphasized the strong, enduring relationship between Singapore and Jiangsu...
